Can't divide directly under mod
Instead: a/b mod p = a * b^(p-2) mod p
power(den, mod-2) = modular inverse of den
So ans = C(n-1, k) mod (1e9+7)

EXAMPLE:
Normal math:   12 / 4 = 3
Mod math:      12 % 7 = 5
               4  % 7 = 4
               5  / 4 = 1.25  ✗  (not an integer, wrong answer)

*******************************************
Mmod = 1000000007;
long ans = (num * power(den, mod-2)) % mod;
